  "type": "Exercise",
  "number": "5.1.4.2.7",
  "title": "",
  "body": "  In the State of Michigan, the amount of state income tax owed is a function of taxable income. The tax rate is a flat of taxable income. Is the amount of Michigan state income tax a linear function of taxable income? Justify your answer.    Yes, it is linear. The amount your tax changes as your income increases is always tax per dollar or income.   "
